Tracking file. Just noting its role: a prioritized markdown backlog for the `ctx-*` toolchain, sorted by impact then difficulty.

Structure: single markdown table with columns `task | description | impact | difficulty`. References `docs/DECISIONS.md` for architectural rationale (ADR numbers cited inline, e.g. ADR-043, ADR-054, ADR-020, ADR-035, ADR-039, ADR-049) and states architecture is derived via `ctx-context .`.

Not code — no functions, no invariants to verify. An editor updating this file should preserve the sort order (impact desc, then difficulty asc) and keep ADR cross-references accurate since several rows describe work that depends on specific ADR decisions still being current. Content is task descriptions for a context-generation/agent-tooling system (crates named `ctx-core`, `ctx-context`, `ctx-scan`, `ctx-summarize`, `ctx-brief`, `ctx-verify`); several entries reference exact file:line locations in that codebase (e.g. `checks.rs:211`, `model.rs:157`, `cli.rs:90`) that would need updating if those files change.